  <main>
    <section id="computers">
      <h2>What Are Computers?</h2>
      <p>A computer is an electronic device that processes data and performs tasks according to a set of instructions called programs.
      It can store, retrieve, and process information quickly and accurately. Computers are used in almost every field nowadays. They help people communicate, solve problems, and create new technologies. All computers share the same goal: to make tasks easier and faster.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="work">
      <h2>How Do Computers Work?</h2>
      <p>Computers work by following instructions from software. When a user gives a command, the computer’s hardware processes it using
      binary code (0s and 1s). The central processing unit (CPU) acts like the brain, executing instructions and managing data. All
      these components work together through the operating system to complete tasks efficiently.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="important">
      <h2>What Is the Most Important Part of a Computer?</h2>
      <p>The most important part of a computer is the <strong>CPU (Central Processing Unit)</strong>. It performs all calculations and controls
      other components. The CPU interprets and executes instructions. Without it, the
      computer cannot function.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="components">
      <h2>What Are the Components of a Computer?</h2>
      <p>A computer system is made up of <strong>hardware</strong> and <strong>software</strong>. Hardware includes physical parts such as the monitor,
      keyboard, mouse, CPU, RAM, hard drive, and motherboard. Software refers to programs and operating systems that tell the hardware
      what to do. All these components work together to perform tasks, store data, and communicate with users.</p>
    </section>

